items.sentence: I don't know if Tom plans on doing that or not.
How do you plan on keeping Tom from doing that?
Didn't you know Tom was planning on doing that?

When I started to do that, Tom told me to stop.
The question is whether Tom can do that or not.
It's doubtful whether Tom will be able do that.
I'd like for Tom to never come back here again.
I'll send Tom there to check the situation out.
I'll send Tom there to check out the situation.
